The paper deals with algorithms for the decremental $(1+\epsilon)$-approximate Single-Source Shortest Path (SSSP) problem and the decremental $(1+\epsilon)$-approximate All-Pairs Shortest Path (APSP) problem, both of which are fundamental problems in computer science and fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also introduces new techniques for cover data structures for graphs, heavy/light decomposition framework, and clustering technique, which are relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG), machine learning (cs.LG), and game theory (cs.GT).
